# Typer environment variables — copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in.
#
# v1 of Typer is a fully client-side static SPA and has NO runtime env vars.
# This file exists so future contributors know how to add them safely.
#
# CONVENTIONS — read before adding a new variable:
#
#  1. Variables prefixed with `VITE_` are inlined into the client bundle at
#     build time and are PUBLIC. Anyone with DevTools can read them.
#     Use VITE_ only for non-secret config (feature flags, public URLs, etc.).
#
#     Example:
#     # VITE_PUBLIC_API_BASE=https://typer.example.com/api
#
#  2. Variables without the `VITE_` prefix are NOT exposed to the client.
#     They are only available in build scripts and (when we add a backend)
#     serverless functions. THIS is where API keys go.
#
#     Example (do not put real values here — only the variable name):
#     # ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
#     # UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
#     # UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=
#
#  3. Never commit a real `.env` or `.env.local`. They are in .gitignore.
#     Rotate any key that ever lands in git history, even if force-pushed away.
